		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As far as reference pages go... to this day I still use obelisk:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.obelisk.demon.co.uk/6502/reference.html">http://www.obelisk.demon.co.uk/6502/reference.html</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />One of the few docs that are actually easy/quick to navigate and is 100% error free.
<br />
<br />For detailed (advanced) operation of each instruction, the charts at the bottom of this doc are a big help:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/6502_cpu.txt">http://nesdev.com/6502_cpu.txt</a><!-- m -->

		

